    "form_header_text": "FY27 Appropriations Request Form (Programmatic & Language Requests)",
    "form_instructions_text": "This form is designed to compile and organize the information necessary to advocate for a programmatic or language request in the fiscal year (FY) 2027 appropriations bill. \n\nThis form is NOT for Community Project Funding (CPF) / Congressionally Directed Spending (CDS) requests. Those requests must be submitted via a separate form, which can be found at the \"Community Project Funding Requests\" section on our website at https://susielee.house.gov/services/appropriations-requests. \n\nPlease note that this form is reviewed by the Office of Congresswoman Susie Lee and completion of this form does not guarantee formal submission to the Appropriations Committee. \n\n*****If your organization has multiple requests, please submit one form per request.*****\n\n- The deadline to submit this form is 6:00 PM ET on Friday, March 6.\n- All fields of this form must be completed.\n- Requests must be merit-based and comply with House rules.\n- Please call our Washington, D.C., office at (202) 225-3252 should you have any questions.\n\nPlease review the below definitions and examples for Programmatic, Report, & Bill Language appropriations requests before beginning this form.\n\n- Programmatic (funding) Language: Requests a funding level for a program within an agency.\n- Report Language: Requests language to be inserted into the Appropriations Committee Report.\n- Bill Language: Requests language to be included directly in an appropriations bill.",
